<BYLINE>
   By CHRISTOPHER PARKES
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
The Bonn economics ministry yesterday announced an unexpected fall in
industrial output in June, following a sharp downward revision of
provisional growth figures for May, writes Christopher Parkes.
Total production last month was 1.5 per cent lower than in May, when
industry recorded 0.7 per cent month-on-month growth, corrected from 1.2 per
cent.
The June figure suggests that there is some way to go before government and
Bundesbank claims that the recession may be drawing to a close can be
substantiated.
