<HEADLINE>
FT  02 AUG 93 / International Capital Markets: Banco Essi opens fund for
foreign investment
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By PETER WISE
</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>
   LISBON
</DATELINE>
<TEXT>
BANCO Essi, part of Espirito Santo, one of Portugal's leading private
financial groups, is launching a Dollars 100m capital development fund in
association with Mr George Soros, the international investor, to invest in
Portugal. It will be five times bigger than any other if its kind in
Portugal.
The lead investor will be Soros Capital II, which will commit about Dollars
50m to the fund. 'Over the years Espirito Santo has developed strategic
relations with new partners,' said Mr Michael de Mello, of the fund's
consultant team. 'That is how we have built ourselves up after being
nationalised in 1975.'
Banco Essi will commit Dollars 7m to the fund. Other backers will be
insurance companies, pension funds and other institutional investors.
The closed-end fund will have two closing dates: one on August 4 at around
Dollars 80m, and a second in November at Dollars 100m.
The fund will typically invest in businesses over which it establishes
control or a significant degree of influence. There will be no hostile
investments and the fund will not invest in the financial or real estate
sectors.
