FT  02 AUG 93 / International Company News: 3M up slightly at Dollars 331m
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
   By KAREN ZAGOR
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
3M, the US manufacturer of adhesives, magnetic tapes and other industrial
and consumer products, turned in second-quarter net income of Dollars 331m,
or Dollars 1.51 a share, writes Karen Zagor.
A year earlier, it earned Dollars 317m, or Dollars 1.45. Sales were
essentially flat at Dollars 3.54bn, up from Dollars 3.52bn.
Mr L. D. DeSimone, chairman, said the company expected higher earnings for
the year as a whole, in spite of a difficult economic environment and
unfavourable currency translations. Like many other companies, 3M is finding
Europe a particularly challenging market.
For the first half, net income was Dollars 661m, or Dollars 3.02, on sales
of Dollars 7.06bn, against earnings of Dollars 623m, or Dollars 2.83, on
sales of Dollars 6.96bn. In the 1992 period, 3M took charges of 2 cents a
share for accounting changes.
