<HEADLINE>
FT  02 AUG 93 / The ERM Crisis: Chequered history of ERM
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
1979
March: Start of the European monetary system and the exchange rate mechanism
1981
October: Lira and French franc devalued by 3 per cent
1983
March: D-Mark revalued upwards by 5.5 per cent
1986
April: D-Mark and Dutch guilder revalued upwards by 3 per cent
1987January: D-Mark and Dutch guilder revalued upwards by 3 per cent and
Belgian franc by 2 per cent
1990
January: Lira moves to narrow band and devalues 3.7 per cent
October: Sterling joins the ERM
1992
April: Portugal joins the ERM
September 13: Lira devalued by 7 per cent
September 16: UK quits the ERM; Spain devalues peseta by 5 per cent; lira
suspended from system until September 22
September 22: Lira quits system indefinitely
November 21: Spanish peseta and Portuguese escudo devalued by 6 per cent
1993
January: Irish punt devalues by 10 per cent
May: Spain and Portugal devalue by 8 per cent and 6.5 per cent respectively
July 30: French franc, Belgian franc and Danish krone pushed to ERM floors
against D-Mark amid heavy speculative selling
</TEXT>
