FT  31 JUL 93 / Consultation on pension proposals
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
THE government is asking for opinions on proposals that could give local
authorities a free hand in setting pension benefits for their staff.
The Department of the Environment proposals would change the local
government superannuation scheme, in England and Wales. Only new employees
would be affected.
More than Pounds 33bn is invested in the scheme.
