FT  31 JUL 93 / World Commodities Prices: Spices
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
Indonesian cassia prices remain firm, reports Man Producten, with a rising
trend in European currency terms. Industrial buyers, however, are holding
back from covering their needs for autumn grinding. Ka/va sticks for spot
delivery are fetching Dollars 2,325 a tonne, with shipment offers at Dollars
2,215. Madagascar and Seychelles cassia prices are unchanged at Dollars
1,100 and Dollars 1,275 a tonne cif respectively. Chinese broken cassia is
on offer at between Dollars 1,300 and Dollars 1,350 a tonne, and for whole
at Dollars 1,500 to Dollars 1,550. Nutmeg and mace prices are unchanged with
S/A bwp at Dollars 700 a tonne, S/A shrivels at Dollars 940, S/A abcd at
